<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbd080d60-76cd-11f0-842a-a3c49cc8bf0c" identifier="/us/usc/t13/s182"><num value="182">§ 182.</num><heading> Surveys</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may make surveys deemed necessary to furnish annual and other interim current data on the subjects covered by the censuses provided for in this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbd080d61-76cd-11f0-842a-a3c49cc8bf0c">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/94/521/s8/a">Pub. L. 94–521, § 8(a)</ref>, <date date="1976-10-17">Oct. 17, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/2463">90 Stat. 2463</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
